Kraken HMAC-SHA512 (_kraken_sign)\par
The algorithm from Kraken's official docs, now verified against their published test vector:\par
SHA256( str(nonce) + urlencode(payload) )  \f8\u8594?  \f7 sha256_bytes\par
HMAC-SHA512( urlpath_bytes + sha256_bytes,  key=base64decode(secret) )  \f8\u8594?  \f7 base64\par
The critical detail is that nonce must be a string before being prepended, and the hmac.new() argument order is (key, message, digestmod) \f8\emdash  \f7 getting those reversed is the most common auth failure.\par
Crypto.com HMAC-SHA256 (_cdc_sign + _cdc_params_to_str)\par
CDC's algorithm requires recursive alphabetical key sorting at every nesting level of the params dict. The dbg6 version fixes the Python closure bug from dbg6's failed attempt. Output is hex (not base64 \f8\emdash  \f7 another common mistake). The signature payload is method + id + api_key + param_str + nonce.\par
Fill-polling state machine (_poll_until_terminal)\par
Polls every FILL_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC (0.5s) until the order reaches a terminal state. Both legs are polled in parallel via asyncio.gather. IOC orders on liquid books resolve in <1s; the 15s timeout is a safety net for exchange latency spikes only.\par
Imbalance recovery\par
If one leg fills and the other doesn't, the engine immediately alerts you with the exact manual action needed (buy/sell the exact quantity to flatten) and stops \f8\emdash  \f7 it does not attempt to withdraw or proceed.\par
